		<p class="contentsubhead" id="1">Overview</p>
		<p class="contenttext">
				MCube is a complete business communication system offering business-class features enabling you to connect all your employees onto one phone system converging all land lines within your office with mobile phones your employees may have. This allows your customers to connect to your business through one point of contact. </p>

			<p class="contenttext">	Mcube Track allows you to improve ROI from ad spend, algorithm based automated call distribution to your executives with fewer missed calls, no busy signals, repeat calls going to last spoken executive etc. This results in higher lead conversion and improves your marketing and sales activities. </p>

				<p class="contenttext">McubeX converges mobile phones and landlines with employee phone extensions into one business system. Easy way for your customers to connect with you and giving your business a professional first impression. </p>
<p class="contenttext">
				MCube IVRS helps you build effective incoming/outgoing voice campaigns, surveys or even a McubeX call. It can also be used to build a Voice Portal that provides information for your products and guide customers who call your number. </p>
			
			
			 </p>
		<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Landing Numbers</p>
		<p class="contenttext">
			A landing number is a number published for a particular service by a business. All the clients of that 		business will call on this number. Once configured, the calls can be routed, recorded accordingly.From a business/user perspective, a landing number is associated to a group. A group is a set of employees providing a service. </p>
			
			<p class="contenttext">A landing number is uniquely assigned to a group i.e. one landing number == one group.
			This landing number is also associated with a package for billing purposes.</p>
		</p>
		<p class="contentsubhead" id="3">Registering Your Business</p>
		<p class="contenttext">To Use Mcube, you need to register your business. This can be done by clicking on ‘signup’ link on the Mcube homepage. </p>
		<p class="contenttext">You have to fill the registration form which has fields like Company Name, Address and phone number. You also need to fill in one user name with email address. This email address/username is the primary login( administrator) for your business. </p>
		<p class="contenttext">Once you have registered successfully, it will take you to the Request OTP page. The One Time Password will Receive by the specified Mail while register and also the Mobile Number which mention in signup page.  </p>
		
		<p class="contenttext"><b>Initial Configuration  of the Business will be taken care by Our Administration Department.</b>
		</p>
