			<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Packages</p>

			<p class="contenttext">The package concept is directed to streamline the  range of services offered for a particular number against the price a customer is paying.  You need admin login to configure it.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">A landing number is associated with a group. While configuring the group, you can choose various options like missed call, record conversation, SMS sent to customer etc. These options are decided based on the package you purchased.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">Add on packages are available if your package is not a default packegr.</p>
				
			<p class="contenttext">Each landing number from the backend is assigned to one of the services (MCube Track, MCube X, MCube IVRS) purchased by you. This landing number will then be mapped to a group within the service by you. When configuring the group for MCube Track or MCube IVRS or MCube X you will setup the options that suite your requirement and when you select landing number the available number for this service will appear. If the number is already in use it will not show during setup of the group. When you select the number some options may not appear. This will depend on the package purchased by you.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">Therefore, when a number is being assigned to you VMC Admin will assign a package to go with it. She/He will also ensure that there are different numbers for call track, IVRS and PBX. One number cannot have all three.</p>
			<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Mcube Track</p>
			<p class="contenttext">VMC's MCube Track is an easy to use Hosted Solution that can track incoming phone calls back to the its origination or source. The analytics will reveal effectiveness by telling you the number of calls generated for a campaign or source. There are no expensive equipment or software required to use powerful features of MCubeTrack.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">MCube Track will automatically track and forward the call coming against each landing number, record the caller's number, time at which call came, duration of the call. If the caller calls more than one then the call gets forwarded to the sales agent that spoke to the caller earlier (If Sticky caller option has been selected). Sales agent can then enter rest of the information like caller name, caller email, remarks of the call etc. to qualify the call. </p>

			<p class="contenttext">The reports have been broken into qualified calls, unqualified calls and missed calls and follow up with your team to get any details and track how sales agents are performing against leads assigned to them and track how each campaign is doing and how many calls have been recorded against each campaign.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">Users of the system can convert selected calls to leads and the calls will start showing in the leads module. This will allow your business to segregate the good calls that can generate potential business from calls that may not generate immediate business for you.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">MCube allows you to add customized fields to call reports or lead reports so you can enter customized data for incoming calls. In some ways MCube Panel will work like a mini CRM for pre-sales management.</p>

			<p class="contenttext">MCube also gives you ability to callback the clients number using “Click2Call” option against each call. On clicking the call will first connect the logged in agent and then the customer. If the customer picks up then the both can talk otherwise the call gets disconnected. You will need to buy MCube Credits for this feature. Please contact our sales team to know how to buy these credits.</p> 
			
			<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">CallTrack Groups </p> 

			<p class="contenttext">CallTrack groups are identifiers for each call source and a landing number is associated to the group. Each group has employees who will attend calls coming in from the associated landing number. Each employee may work certain hours or serve certain region and based on the time of the work and region they serve the incoming call will be connected to the employees within the group. To be able to take call the employee should be confirmed employee and not disabled. If you observe an employee is not getting calls then check the following:
			<ul class="bulletpoints">
					<li> Employee should not be disabled. Go to employee listing and check for lock sign against the employee.</li>
					<li>The employee working hours fall within the time at which the call is coming. Go to employee listing click on employee to check the hours employee works.</li>
					<li>If the employee is not in the employee list then employee has not confirmed, go to uncomfirmed employee list and if the employee is present in this list then ask the employee to confirm from its email.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="contenttext">The employees with in group will receive calls based on routing algorithm selected, there are two different rules, to route the calls to employees.
				<ul class="bulletpoints">
					<li>Sequential: The call will be routed to employees in sequential order which employees are added</li>
					<li>Weighted: Based on the priority or weight-age which we will assign to group employees, call will be route to that.</li>
				</ul>
			</p>
			<p class="contenttext">Every group contains one Group Owner. The Group Owner will act as a 'Fail over'. means, if no one picks up the call, default it will go to the Group Owner.( Even if he is NOT shown in the employee list of the group.). You can configure such that group owner does not get a call.</p>
			<p class="contenttext"><b>Fail Over:</b> If we have assign or group to “Fail over”, that list of employees will not comes under the call routing system, If all the employees of call routing or diverting are not able to receive the call, that time Fail over employee list will get call(as group rules, it may be sequential or weighted). </p>
			<p class="contenttext">If none of the fail over employees pick up the call then the call goes to the Group owner, if this person is also does not pick the call, then the call will go to voice mail if voice mail option is selected otherwise the call will disconnect and call is reported as missed call.</p>
