		<p class="contenttext"> List of MCube X which we delete from the list of PBX. We can restore it, if its required.</p>
		<p class="contenttext"> <b>How It works:</b>
			<ul class="bulletpoints">
				<li>Once a call comes on the landing number configured for PBX, the recorded message is  played ( if the recorded file is uploaded).</li> 
				<li>It waits for the caller to punch-in the extension number. If a valid extension number is input, the call will be transferred to the number configured for that employee. The first extension is NOT preceded by a “*” or a “#” sign. For subsequent transfers the extension number has to be preceded by either “*” [the present extension will not be disconnected] or “#” [the present extension will be disconnected].</li>
				<li>If not a valid extension number it gets transferred to the PBX Operator.</li>
				<li>The directory services can be used if the caller doesn’t know the extension number. To access Directory services, ‘1’ has be pressed. Then the caller will be prompted to press the first three characters of the name of the person he wants to connect to. All the names corresponding to this input will be available for selection one by one. If there are no names corresponding to the input, the call will be routed to the operator.</li> 
				<li>If the direct operator is enabled, all the calls are routed directly to the operator and no input is accepted. Directory services will also not work in this case.</li>
				<li>Any of the employees can also be made the PBX operator by clicking at the action icon against the employee extension in the McubeX. Then this employee will act as the direct operator.</li>
			</ul>
		</p>	
