		<p class="contenttext">The system allows sending ad-hoc SMS to a particular number from the system. This report gives details of all such SMS send.</p> 
		<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Follow ups Report: </p>
		<p class="contenttext">A follow up can be set up in the system against any number to remind the executive to follow up. This can be either on mail or sms or both. The default report gives the details of the future followups put in the system. Older follow ups can be seen by using the serach option.</p> 
		<p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Break History:</p>
		<p class="contenttext">This report gives the details of the employees that were on break and for which duration.</p> 	
			
		 <p class="contentsubhead">Enhancements made in September 2013 Release :</p>
		<p class="contenttext">
			<p>1. Changes to Report UI<br/>
			MCube reports are more dynamic now. There are changes to the User Interface so you now see three new tabs : ‘All’ , ‘Basic’, ‘Contact’.  The default is ‘All’ which is the same report as earlier. The ‘Basic’ report has the following fields :<br/>
			From | Group | To | Date Time | Duration | Pulse | Call Status | Remarks<br/>
			The ‘Contact’ report has the following fields :<br/>
			From | Group | To | Date Time | Duration | Name | Address | Email | Remarks<br/>
			The records displayed in all these reports are the same, only it’s easier to find specific information. <br/>
			In addition, the user has an option of creating and saving  his own customized reports. The customized reports can be created and saved in the ‘Advanced Search’ . Once these reports are saved they will come up as tabs in the report section along with ‘All’,’Basic’, ‘Contact’.<br/>
			For example: “Last 7 Days” is the one in below screen.<br/><br/>
			<img src="system/application/img/icons/reports-ui.jpeg" />
			<p>2. New fields added to the Track Report: Some new fields like duration, Reference id and Unique id have to added to the report. Duration is the time in seconds for which the call was made. Earlier the time was only reported in pulse. Unique id an automatically generated sequential number assigned  to every incoming call .It’s unique and  not editable/changeable. Reference id is also similar and by default it is same as the unique id but this field is editable so the executive could put any reference id to identify this call .</p>
			<p>3. Advance search: A new ‘Advance Search’ is available in the search section. This allows more flexibility as it offers users to put in their customized filters. This search can also be saved as a customized report.<br/>
			The three main reports, Track report, IVRS Report, McubeX  report and the Leads module  have an ‘Advanced search’ tab  in the search option. <br/>
			This option allows the user more options to narrow the search or to design a specific report [by saving the search as a report]. <br/>
			The report offers Time filters like All, today, last 7 days or this month.<br/>
			Group and employee selection <br/>
			It also has an option to add a ‘AND’ or ‘OR’ condition on all the fields of that report.<br/>
			<img src="system/application/img/icons/advsearch.jpeg"/>
			</p>
			<p>4. Bulk download: Bulk download option in the report allows downloading only the selected records.</p>
			<p>5. Convert lead/Update Lead: This option is now available as a checkbox on edit action on a call. Once checked , the user can covert this call into a lead and assign it either to a group or an employee. All calls converted into leads are visible in green color. For more details see the Leads Management section.</p>
			<p>6. Remark History: Earlier the remarks entered against a particular call were not visible in the next call from the same number. Now a remark history is maintained where all the remarks from the previous calls  from the same number are appended and  visible in the lastest call from the same number.</p>
		</p>
		 <p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Admin : </p>  

		<p class="contenttext">This will be available for the role of Administration employees for the business. In this mode of role, employee can view overall process with of “Edit Profile”, ”Manage System Label”, ”New Role”, ”List Role”, ”Audit trail”, ”Region Algo Names”, ”Blacklist Numbers”.</p> 

		<p class="contenttext">Individual in this role will be able to see all calls through all groups within the account.</p> 

		<p class="contenttext">Individual with this role can create new role, edit entitlements for different roles, assign roles to employees etc.</p> 

		<p class="contenttext">Individual with this role that edit title of fields in reports, Add new customized fields, remove fields for a view and these can also be done at role level.
		<br/>
		
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/adminprofile.png"/>
		</p> 
		
		
		 <p class="contenttext"><b>	Edit Profile:</b> </p> 
		<p class="contenttext">To edit  the business profile. OTP filed will be for One Time Password alert, for users while logging in  for that particular session.</p> 
		<p class="contenttext"><b>Related Business:</b> This will give the Child Businesses of the existing business. Existing business will act as a </p> 
		<p class="contenttext">Parent business. And the administration employee will be able to see the child businesses, employees, Groups, calls report, follow ups and everything.</p> 
		<p class="contenttext">Parent-Child relationship is only for group of businesses in which one business is parent of other businesses. This is not applicable for most cases.</p> 

		 <p class="contenttext"><b>Manage System Label:</b></p> 

		<p class="contenttext">This is the Module to Add the custom fields related to business. System fields will be defined and allocated at initial stage(our Support team will take care).</p> 
		<p class="contenttext">Under this category we are having the below list, I mean we can add the custom fields for the given list.</p> 
		<p>Business Profile<br/>Employee Module<br/>Group Module<br/>IVRS System<br/>IVRS Options<br/>Call Report<br/>IVRS Report<br/>Virtual PBX<br/>Contacts<br/>Pbx Report<br/>Click to Call<br/>Leads<br/>Email<br/>Holiday<br/>Leads Followup<br/>Employee Breakhistory<br/>Leads Groups</p> 
		<p class="contenttext">We can able to create the custom field to the above list, and that fields have to be check with the role, then only the field will be presented at the part. We have to be enter the Label name, label type, label values, label default value, is required. We can able to select the custom field type as Text, Text area, Radio, Checkbox, Dropdown.</p> 

	<p class="contenttext" ><b>New Role:</b></p> 

	<p class="contenttext">This is the area which allows business to create customized roles related to business with different access levels. There are few default roles that can also be modified by admin user.</p> 

	<p class="contenttext"><b>New role can be created with access level for:</b> Business Profile,Employee,Groups,MCube IVRS,IVRS option,Track Report,MCube IVRS Report,MCube X,Contact Module,PBX Report,Click to Call,Leads,Email,Holiday,Leads Followup,Employee Breakhistory,Leads Groups
	<br/>
	<img src="system/application/img/icons/newrole.png"/>
	
	
	</p>
	<p class="contenttext" ><b>List Role:</b></p>
	<p class="contenttext">This will give the list of all the roles for that business. It includes, system roles as well as new roles. We can not delete the roles, once its been created. We can edit the system predefined roles and change the access levels.</p>
	<p class="contenttext">It gives the list of S.No, Role Name, Record Limit, Action. Under action only edit option will be presented.
	<br/>
	<img src="system/application/img/icons/rlist.png"/>
	
	</p>
	
	<p class="contenttext" ><b>Audit Trail:</b></p>
		<p class="contenttext">This is the log file all the users. This gives view to all the activity and employees actions, performed within this account, with Username, Module Name, Action, Date & Time. </p>

	<p class="contenttext" ><b>Region Algo Names:</b></p>
	<p class="contenttext">List of Region names to create the groups. If we select particular region, only that region calls can be handeled. We are listing as number, region Algo name, Action. Under action, edit the region, add new Region , and listing of groups to that particular region.</p>
	<p class="contenttext" ><b>Block List Numbers:</b></p>
	<p class="contenttext">This will gives the list of all the blocked numbers. If call comes from number in this list then it will not flow to anyone within the group and the call will drop.</p>

	 <p class="contenttext">“Add block number” form under 'Home' Menu allows you to add numbers in block list.</p>

	<p class="contenttext" ><b>Search Criteria </b></p>
	<p class="contenttext">There is a search option for reporting system, to find the incoming, attended calls.
	<br/>
	<img src="system/application/img/icons/search_c.png"/>
	
	
	</p>
	
	<p class="contenttext">Search can be accessed by clicking on the Icon at top right. This will open up the form with fields like, call from, start time, end time, employees, caller name, address, email, business and in extra Custom field, if any thing presented for the business. It will give all the matched records.
	
	
	</p>
	 <p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Dash Board :</p>

	<p class="contenttext">MCube Dashboard shows call activity of last 7 days.</p>

	<p class="contenttext">If you are a group owner,[ irrespective of the fact that you appear or not in the  employee list for that group], you will be able to see all the calls coming to that group and you will be the default ‘fail over’.</p>
