 <p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Lead Management :</p>

	<p class="contenttext">Leads Module is the Module to revise the Pre-sale information or convert the existing calls as leads.<br/>
		Leads can be added to this module either manually by executives/employees (upload option available if the number of leads is more) or existing call in the system can be converted as leads. <br/>
		A concept of Leads group similar to the groups in call track is introduced. This group is specific to the leads section and contains employees/executives.<br/>
		A lead can be assigned to either an employee or to a group. Bulk assignment of leads is also possible.
		If bulk leads are assigned to a group, the group rule (sequential or weighed) decides how the leads are distributed among the employees of the group.<br/><br/>
		<b>Lead Groups:</b><br/>
		The Lead group is as same as call track group. The Employees/ Executives will come under groups. The lead groups has two basic rules i.e sequential and weighted. According to this rule or algorithm the employees will be assign to leads. <br/><br/>
		<b>Lead Groups:</b><br/>
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/addleadgrp.jpeg"/>
		Add Lead Group Form contains the groupname, grouprule, groupowner and groupdescription.<br/><br/>
		<b>List Lead Groups:</b><br/>
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/listleadgrp.jpeg"/><br/>
		List all the Lead groups details along with Actions like Edit, Delete, AddEmployee, List Employee.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-plus"></span>: Add Employee to Group, as like adding Employees to Call track group.<br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span>: List of Employees in that group.<br/><br/>
		<b><h2>Leads:</h2></b><br/>
		<p>This shows all the direct lead entries as well as converted leads.<br/>
		This has sub menu of ,'Add lead','List Leads','Deleted Leads'.<br/>
		<b>Add Lead</b><br/>
		Add lead form will give the ability to put the caller details / leads details directly on to the System. 
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/addlead.jpeg"/><br/>
		<b>Group:</b> Select the group which the lead is belongs to. This list comes from leads groups.<br/>
		<b>Assignto:</b> Select the Assignto Employee, which the lead is assigned. This will be the group employees, after selecting the above group.<br/>
		<b>Name:</b> Caller Name.<br/>
		<b>Email:</b> Caller Email.<br/>
		<b>Number:</b> Call From Number. <br/>
		<b>Source:</b> This is the source from where we got the lead, if the lead is converted from manage incoming caller, the source should be calltrack in default and its not editable.<br/>
		<b>Caller Business:</b> Caller business information<br/>
		<b>Caller Address: </b>Caller contact information.<br/>
		<b>Remark:</b> This is the remark or comment on the call, while converting lead from incoming caller, all the remarks presented in that call will be update automatically.<br/>
		<b>Reference Id:</b> To identify the incoming caller from the report, this may be duplicate.<br/>
		<b>Status:</b> It defines the lead status as, lead is open, pending,closed won, closed lost, waiting for customer response.<br/><br/>
		<b>List Leads</b><br/>
		<p>
		It lists all the active leads presented in the system. It has search module,Download feature, Bulk Assignment, Bulk Delete, Bulk Email And Bulk SMS.<br/>
		Below are the icons of those tasks.<br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-download-alt"></span>:  This indicates the download feature of module. Opens a popup to give the conditions. Denotes 'Start Download' Link, need to download from there.<br/>
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/group.png"/>: This indicates to assign one or more number of leads to individual employee or group. If selects group leads will follow the group algorithm.<br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-trash"></span>: This indicates bulk delete. Delete task for one or more records.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-envelope-o"></span>:Bulk Email sending. Emails goes from the mail id specified in Email – configuration.<br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-comment"></span>:Bulk SMS sending.<br/><br/>
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/listleads.jpeg"/><br/>
		<b>Actions in Leads</b><br/>
		<span class="fa fa-edit"></span>: To edit the lead<br/>
		<img src="system/application/img/icons/group.png"/>:Delete operation on leads<br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user"></span>: This shows the lead details with followups and comments.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span>:List the follow ups for specific lead and form to enter the follow up.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-envelope"></span>:Sending the email if the caller email presented. <br/>
		<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-comment"></span>:SMS will be sent to the specified caller number.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-phone"></span>:Connect to the caller number with the person who logged into the system.<br/>
		<span class="fa fa-comment"></span>:List of comments and the form to create comment.<br/><br/>
		</p>
		</p>
	</p>
	 <p class="contentsubhead" id="2">Convert Lead :</p>
	 <p class="contenttext">
		 Convert lead option is available as a checkbox in  Reports->Manage incoming caller ->Update the details section. Once this box is checked, an option will be available to either assign it to an individual employee or to a group. There is also an option to send an alert via email, sms or both to the employee/group that is being assigned the lead.<br/>
		 If only the lead group  is selected the assignment to the employees in that group will be according to  the group algorithm.<br/>
		 <b>Convert as lead or Update as lead</b><br/>
		 When a lead is converted, the option of convert lead in the call track report will change to update lead. Any changes made in the call report( like the remarks field ) will be reflected in the leads section if the ‘update lead’ checkbox is checked.<br/>
		 A call is associated with an incoming number, group.<br/>
		 A lead is also associated with an incoming number, employee and a leads group.<br/>
		 After a lead is converted, another call from the same incoming number can come into the system.
		 <ul class="bulletpoints">
			 <li>If this call is associated with the different group of call track  then the convert lead option will be available again. If while converting, the same leads group as the previous converted call is assigned is selected , then these two leads will be merged and appear as one. Only the call counter in the leads section will increment. All the call history will be shown when the counter is clicked.</li>
			 <li>If while converting, a different lead group is selected then it will treated as a separate lead.</li>
		 </ul>
		 <b>Update Lead:</b><br/>
		 <p>when you try to edit the already converted lead call, will get 'Update lead' option, then it will update the caller details with remark. And remarks will give concatenation of all remark history.</p><br/>
		 <br/>
		 Convert Lead <br/>
		 <img src="system/application/img/icons/convertlead.jpeg"/><br/><br/>
		 Update Lead<br/>
		 <img src="system/application/img/icons/updatelead.jpeg"/><br/><br/>

	 </p>
